{% block page_shell_content_intro %}
    {% filter markdown %}
        <h1>Dialog</h1>

        <p class="spirit-subhead">A dialog is a temporary contextual UI element that overlays the web page or application content and provides information to the user and, often, requires user input. When these overlays are active or open, interactions with the web page or application are disabled until the overlay is closed or required interaction is completed.</p>
        <p>Dialogs are disruptive intentionally and should be used thoughtfully and sparingly depending on the informational context and/or need.</p>
        <p>Dialogs depend on Javascript. We are leveraging [A11y Dialog](https://edenspiekermann.github.io/a11y-dialog/) within the Spirit design system to run the dialogs. See [Guidelines - JavaScript](/#) for information javascript usage and the necessary dependencies.</p>
